<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="460" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.51/675: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HEL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harris</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">temporarily at Omsk</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-30T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 30,
                                        1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your September 20, 10 a.m.<note n="76" xml:id="d460fn76">Transmitted in
                                telegram from the Chargé in China, Sept. 22, <ref target="#pg_430">p. 430</ref>.</note> Loan has since gone through in regular
                            course.</p>
                        <p>Department did everything possible in circumstances and told bankers we
                            were committed to support <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>